The paper discusses distributionally robust optimization (DRO) in the context of machine learning, specifically in kernel methods. This makes it likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper discusses connections to regularization and generalization, which are also key topics in cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.STAT (Statistics). The paper also mentions Gaussian kernel ridge regression, which is commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV). Finally, the paper discusses a generically applicable approximation of MMD DRO, which could potentially be applied to other areas of computer science, such as control systems (cs.SY).
